se it.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg, Real Love: The Art of Mindful Connection\n|\nThe money you are looking for is not in any country, phd or your designer outlook, it is in wisdom. Solomon never prayed for wealth but he asked for wisdom.\n\n- Patience Johnson, Why Does an Orderly God Allow Disorder\n|\nTo respect the dignity of a relationship also implies accepting the end when it comes. Except in my mind, except in my dreams, where the aftertaste of her still lingers.\n\n- André Brink, Before I Forget\n|\nI swear that girl was born with a pen in her hand, the moon in her hair, and stars in her soul.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nUntil you have suffered much in your heart, you cannot learn humility.\n\n- Thaddeus of Vitovnica, Our Thoughts Determine Our Lives:  The Life and Teachings of Elder Thaddeus of Vitovnica\n|\nIf the road to your dreams is full of potholes, take the highway.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nAlthough time is equally possessed by everyone, it is valued and used differently by the successful.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, Unlocking Life's Treasure Chest: Wisdom keys to keep you inspired, encouraged, motivated and focused\n|\nIntelligence...[is] not marathon rac[e]: there is no fixed criteria for success, no start or finish lines -- and running sideways or backwards, might secure victory.\n\n- Siddhartha Mukherjee, The Gene: An Intimate History\n|\nSo, have a little fun. Soon enough you'll be dead and burning in Hell with the rest of your family.\n\n- George Carlin, Brain Droppings\n|\nDown the hill I went, and then,I forgot the ways of men,For night-scents, heady and damp and coolWakened ecstasy\n\n- Sara Teasdale, Flame and Shadow\n|\nIf every mortal looks at others as their friends, not as their enemies, the world would be a much better place, wouldn't it?\n\n- Morgan Rhodes, Frozen Tides\n|\n...That's why we have the Museum, Matty, to remind us of how we came, and why: to start fresh, and begin a new place from what we had learned and carried from the old.\n\n- Lois Lowry